  "text": "The computational cost of coordinate descent algorithm [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] and iterative thresholding algorithm [CITATION_3] for [CITATION_4] and (7) is also O(np) per iteration. The cluster points of sequences generated by CD and iterative thresholding also satisfy (15)- [CITATION_5] . But the convergence rate of these two type of algorithms is at best sub-linear even in the case of LASSO penalized problem where the object function is convex [CITATION_6] . Hence it is not surprising that Algorithms 2 and 3 outperform CD-type algorithms in accuracy and efficiency, see, numerical results in Section 4.",
